Subject Re Novell From Nick FitzGerald PC Software Consultant CSC UoC NZ In article Thomas J Bilan writes If I put LASTDRIVE Z in my NETX will run but I can't access drive f to log in to If I don't put LASTDRIVE Z in my I can't access other drives from the file It seems that there should be a way to make NETX work with the LASTDRIVE statement in my First off I haven't used but I think that's about to change The problem is the LASTDRIVE command and the way NetWare in general and in this case NETX in particular adds drives to the device Setting LASTDRIVE Z means there are no unassigned as opposed to unused drive letters for NetWare to use as it tacks its drive mappings onto the end of the existing list of obviously attaches its network drives to existing unused drive I'd guess the next thing I'd try is something like LASTDRIVE M which on most machines will leave a fair swathe of drives for and still allow up to NetWare drive mappings as Nick FitzGerald PC Applications Consultant CSC Uni of Canterbury TEL FAX